modules.description: Converts runtime errors to strings, manages monadic operations, and performs file system tasks like reading, writing, and checking file existence. Works with custom error types, monadic computations, and path structures. Executes shell commands, logs messages at different levels, and handles file metadata such as modification times and directory contents.

Provides functions to manage and execute build processes, including initializing a development environment and triggering builds. Operates with configuration files and project directories. Used to set up isolated build contexts and compile projects efficiently.

Handles error conversion, monadic operations, and file system interactions, including reading, writing, and metadata retrieval. Supports custom error types, shell command execution, and logging. Processes paths and directory contents, enabling robust file management. Allows for structured error handling and asynchronous task coordination.
